===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|storm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|storm||a storm, tempest; a storm of arrows; disturbance, disquiet; uproar, tumult; rush, onrush, attack, violent attack}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*sturmaz||storm}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*(s)twer-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*(s)tur-||to rotate, swirl, twirl, move around}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|storm||storm}}, {{cog|fy|stoarm||storm}}, {{cog|nl|storm||storm}}, {{cog|nds|storm||storm}}, {{cog|de|Sturm||storm}}, {{cog|da|storm||storm}}, {{cog|sv|storm||storm}}, {{cog|is|stormur||storm}}. Related to {{l|en|stir}}.

